@startuml
title AIOps Codex Current Architecture

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor User

node "Browser\nhttp://127.0.0.1:18080" as Browser

node "Local Machine\n(macOS)" as LocalHost {
  package "AIOps Codex Project" {
    component "ai-server\n(.data/bin/ai-server)" as AIServer
    component "web/dist\nStatic frontend assets" as WebDist
    component "codex app-server\n(subprocess)" as CodexApp
    component "server-local workspace\n~/.aiops_codex" as Workspace
    file "State Store\n.data/ai-server-state.json" as StateFile
    file "Audit Log\n.data/ai-audit.log" as AuditLog
  }

  package "launchd" {
    component "com.aiopscodex.ai-server" as LaunchdAIServer
    component "com.aiopscodex.host-agent" as LaunchdHostAgent
  }
}

node "Agent Host\n(agent-local / future remote host)" as AgentNode {
  component "host-agent" as HostAgent
}

cloud "OpenAI / ChatGPT" as OpenAI

User --> Browser : Use the web UI
Browser --> AIServer : HTTP API + WebSocket
AIServer --> WebDist : Serve frontend assets
LaunchdAIServer --> AIServer : Start and keep alive

AIServer --> CodexApp : stdio JSON-RPC\ninitialize / thread/start / turn/start
CodexApp --> OpenAI : Model session / auth / inference
CodexApp --> Workspace : Read/write workspace\nserver-local operations

AIServer --> StateFile : Persist session / auth / host state
AIServer --> AuditLog : Append audit events

HostAgent --> AIServer : gRPC register / heartbeat
LaunchdHostAgent --> HostAgent : Start and keep alive

note right of CodexApp
Current deployment:
- Runs on the same machine as ai-server
- Started by ai-server as a subprocess
- Not deployed as a separate remote service
end note

note bottom of AgentNode
Current MVP scope:
- host-agent is mainly used for host registration,
  online status, and heartbeat display
- Full remote execution is not completed yet
end note

@enduml
